9:
Why... Why did it have to come to
this...
12:
They keep taking and taking from
me...
16:
I've had enough... If I can't have it all
back, then—
30:
Yes. I'm Stella, and we're in Starview
Village.
32:
It's safe here. You have nothing to be
afraid of.
37: I must've been dreaming... I'm sorry.
42:
I don't mean to be rude, but I'd like
to be alone...
46:
Nasir still won't come out of her
room, huh?
49:
Even so, we cannot simply leave her
alone. There's no telling when she
may go on her next rampage.
53:
We oughta at least take that sword
away from her.
56:
Except she gets extremely defensive
whenever we try to do that.
60:
I would advise against it. Taking
away something she's so attached
to might only do more harm—
69:
Nasir's not in her room or anywhere
in the village!
74:
Tch... Let's move! There's only one
place she'd go off to!
77:
I-it's you, Nasir! Why have you
returned?!
83:
Damn you! Forget about detaining
her! Kill the girl!
86: I told you to step aside...
89: DO NOT GET IN MY WAY!
93:
This is unforgivable... You all deserve
to burn!
94: Burn until you're nothing but ashes!
97:
N-no! Stop this, Nasir! I admit I was
wrong!
99:
I can set you free! Please, just spare
me!
101:
Freedom's what you want, right? You
can be free if you become my wife!
I'll even give you your own slaves!
What do you say?!
108:
Is that the price to pay for freedom?
Is that what it takes to live?
111:
No, I don't think so... I don't need
anything, and neither do you!
114: I'D RATHER SEE YOU SINGED TO ASHES!
125:
I know it's not my place to butt in,
but you'd best stop right there, Nasir.
126:
Offing that filth ain't gonna bring
you any satisfaction.
133:
I don't. What I DO know is that I'm not
gonna just stand by and watch
while you kill yourself along with
those bastards.
136:
You're better at this, Stella. I'll leave
you to do the talkin'.
159:
Thank you so much! You've saved
us...
165:
They're former slaves like yourself. 
I guess those in regions opposing 
the royal family make for easy targets.
169:
Heh. Good thing you didn't burn the
whole place down, eh?
172: Um... Could you tell us your name?
178:
I'm Elisha. Nasir, I'll never forget what
you've done for us. Thank you!
